<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="435" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d435">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hirsch</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-04-28"><hi rend="italic">April 28,
                            1892</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 321.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department fully approves the terms of
                        your note of the 12th instant, a copy of which accompanies your No. 427 of
                        that date, whereby you call for the protection of certain citizens of the
                        United States, engaged as teachers in the district of Gavour, who have been
                        molested by the authorities there.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>